    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artistic aesthetic developed by John Weichsel, influenced by the writings of the German art historian Wilhelm Worringer, and steeped in anarchist philosophy. The Cosmist aesthetic was put into practice by such artists as Elie Nadelman and Adolf Wolff.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
